snippet.textDisplay:
Ohai! For a change a few personal words. My name is Philipp and I started this channel almost seven years ago – you don’t know my voice but you have heard my words because I write most of our scripts.

Oh boy. This was a hard video to make. Gratitude felt vaguely risky to do as a topic. It has this aura of cheap Instagram hashtag self help stuff.

Some of you will hate this video deeply, and the thought of that made me pretty anxious writing it. Gratitude was not supposed to be a video topic originally. Just like the Nihilism and Loneliness videos, the script was based on personal struggles and part of the process of dealing with them. And so it felt right to make gratitude a video too.

But Kurzgesagt is not a self help channel, so we'll keep this sort of content at roughly one or two per year.

We hope they are helpful to some of you.

If you care for my take on how to practice Gratitude, we made a Kurzgesagt Gratitude journal to combine the science with practical tips. https://shop.kurzgesagt.org/

Please note: You don’t need to buy this or anything else to practice gratitude – you only need a pen, a piece of paper and 5 minutes.

Thank you for watching our videos and reading this comment. Being able to do Kurzgesagt means a lot. To me and the whole team. – Philipp

snippet.textDisplay: That last part, “your life could be much more difficult” and for a lot of people it is. There are people starving, no car to go to work, no one to talk to, no job, deep into drugs. Or even harder, physical disabilities, diseases and illnesses that will always limit them. And they wonder what its like to be like us, whole and healthy. Some of us reading this might be one of the very people in that position but they must never give up. We have been given the Gift of Life, intelligence, complex emotion and understanding. We cannot take it for granted. For those seriously struggling, I can only tell you that I myself am struggling with the very thing this video talks about. Dissatisfaction. Its constant, everyday i got through it, i put myself down because i am a perfectionist and im not exactly or more than half of what i really want to be. I think about myself dying everyday. Because thats how dissatisfied I am. But im writing this because im realizing that i shouldnt be. I have a car, a job, a family, people to talk to, and most importantly, im healthy. Maybe im just an ungrateful asshole that just wants to have everything without truly working for it. But i have my reasons. We all do. So im writing this to tell you all that im going to wake up tomorrow and be grateful, thankful, and satisfied with the Gift I have been given, and you should do the same too. Give yourself that chance and never look back. Light your fire and take yourself to places you thought you could never reach. And it may not be perfect, you might begin to feel down again. But you have to get up and try again. Keep failing until you get it right but NEVER give up. Failure is what makes us human if it didnt we’d live in a perfect world. If you have dreams, then go make them come true. It starts with you. Have a great day whoever ends up reading until the end. Much love and power to you. 💪🏼

snippet.textDisplay: During my final year as a student, I was going through a really rough time. That was when I started writing down the people I was grateful for each month, and why I was grateful for them. It really helped me regulated my emotional state, and helped me get along better with my group mates and I generally felt better. Things were still tough of course, but it was a lot easier to pull through when I started being grateful for all the little things around me rather than hyper focusing on the negative life events.
